title: -Gamma-Ray Production Cross Section for Interaction of 14.8 Mev Neutrons With O, Na, Al, Cl, Cr, Fe, Ni, Cu and Pb-.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Jour. of Nuclear Science and Technology, Vol.15, Issue.11, p.797 (1978)

x4freetext: OF 14.8 MEV NEUTRONS WITH O, NA, AL, CL, CR, FE, NI,
THE T(D,N)HE-4 REACTION USING A SOLID TI-T
.METAL SAMPLES OF NATURAL ABUNDANCES, 3 CM IN DIA AND
4 CM HIGH FOR AL, FE, NI AND PB.
.SAMPLES FOR O, NA, CL AND CR WERE PREPARED BY ENCAP-
SULATING WATER, POWDERS OF NACL AND CR-OXIDE AN AL
CANS OF 1 MM THICK WALLS, 3 CM INNER DIA AND 4 CM
COUNTING OF THE HE-4 PARTICLES IN THE NEUTRON
PRODUCING REACTION TO MONITOR THE NEUTRON FLUX.
DETECTOR TO DETECT THE GAMMA RAYS.
A SILICON SURFACE BARRIER DETECTOR TO COUNT
THE HE-4 PARTICLES IN THE NEUTRON PRODUCING REACTION.
A.P.T. JAPAN CODE CHANGED TO JPN
-NEUTRON ATTENUANTION IN THE BACKING AND COOLING
ASSEMBLY OF THE NEUTRON TARGET (5.6 PERCENT),
-NEUTRON MULTIPLE SCATTERING IN THE SAMPLE, USING A
.THE ERRORS WERE ESTIMATED TAKING INTO ACCOUNT THE
-DETERMINING THE NUMBER OF COUNTS IN THE FULL ENERGY
-DETERMINING THE NEUTRON FLUX INCIDENT UPON THE
PEAKS (+- 5 PERCENT FOR E-GAMMA LESS THAN 3 MEV AND
.THE TYPICAL ERRORS OF THE CROSS SECTIONS ARE +- 10
PERCENT FOR SIGMA GREATER THAN 30 MB/SR, +- 17 PER-
CENT FOR SIGMA BETWEEN 10 AND 30 MB/SR AND +- 35
PERCENT FOR SIGMA LESS THAN 10 MB/SR.
